A panel van transporting R200 000 worth of counterfeit cooking yeast and sanitary pads to Nelson Mandela Bay was intercepted by police on Friday morning.
Police spokesman Captain Andre Beetge said a police vehicle from Kinkelbos Police Station had been patrolling the N2 when a panel van without number plates was spotted heading towards the Bay at about 9am.


“The vehicle was pulled off and police found suspicious cargo items in the vehicle. The vehicle and contents were taken to Kinkelbos police station, where customs officials identified the goods as counterfeit, with an estimated value of R200 000,” he said.
“The goods – 180 boxes of sanitary pads and 29 boxes of yeast – were being transported from Johannesburg to Nelson Mandela Bay.”
The 27-year-old driver was arrested and will be appearing before the Alexandria Magistrate’s Court on Monday.


